Date: 0/0/1981
Source:
Author:
Vol / Page:
Edition:
Quote: LOUGHNAN Glossary II 3 wing leader: a dog, really only needed much in the early days of no fences, which travelled not at the head but at the flank of a driven mob tucking back any animals liable to stray aside. A good leader nowadays is often intelligent enough to watch for side roads, broken fences and open gates, and to scamper back without being bidden to reclaim anything that does stray aside.
